We played our first show as @spacemesa last Saturday. It was April 1st so I figured there was a chance it could all be an elaborate April fool’s joke and they wouldn’t let us in the door. It wasn’t. We had one of the most fun nights ever. 
We celebrated @aricav ‘s bday and raised money for the @tortamtb trail system on the Oregon Coast. 
We opened for Josh’s band, Lunker and did 8 songs (5 originals and 3 covers) before we mixed the two bands for 3 more songs. Then, Lunker proceeded to tear the roof off the place until the bar closed. 
Thanks Josh and Arica for being the magnet of good times. Thanks @boneemccaul for coming to the show and having fun, and for putting up with your husband coming to bed way too late after rehearsals over the past couple months. Thanks @therealclouds for passing along this @chevy_metal shirt years ago cuz you knew I’d love it. The shirt has powers.
And thanks @dustywygle , @sports_doug ,and Josh @brosandhoeslandscaping for bringing these songs to life in a room full of ears and eyes attached to our friends’ heads. Can’t wait to do it again. 
——————-
I’ll post vids on the @spacemesa Insta and YouTubes once we get the footy

So… I broke my leg. Seemed like a mellow slide-out until I slid into a rock. It broke my tibial plateau and I had it plated back together. On the mend now. Got a cool scar. Looking forward to being healthy again and grateful this seems to be a straightforward injury. Resting now, rehabbing soon. Thanks for reading.

This surfaced on @pinkbike yesterday. It’s my submission to the RaceFace Ultimate Freeride Challenge video contest from 2003. I was 16 when this was shot. I ended up making it to the final round and getting second place to my now ‘ol buddy @mattyhunter —  This is what started my career in this mountain bike world. I wasn’t sure if this clip still existed, and it was really cool to watch it again after all these years.

I was enjoying getting my 3’s dialed in the day before breaking my leg

A bike festival, a music festival, and a beer festival…. Well those are the 3 best things I can think of and this festival caters to all of them. Soooo, Yes please! I can’t wait to check out the @nwtuneup —
If you also enjoy these 3 things, check out the link in my bio for more info on the Northwest Tune-Up in Bellingham Washington.
Hope to see you there.
#NWTuneUp #AllTunedUp

Having the best time out here at the @nwtuneup — bikes, music, beer — all the good stuff, but hands down my favorite part is watching my daughter take it all in and realize she likes this scene and enjoys “being a biker.”
——-
#AllTunedUp

I had so much fun at the @nwtuneup festival — I was able to emcee the events at the venue and also had the chance to get some riding in. Feels great to be back on the bike. Still have some work to do building strength in the leg and need a couple more weeks of bone-healing but it was a nice taste of what I’ve been missing. Also, kids were ripping at the jump jam… insane. Look out Emil.
